WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

00:00:03.437 --> 00:00:06.306
I want first place
in the debut song ranking

00:00:06.373 --> 00:00:07.474
no matter what!

00:00:07.975 --> 00:00:10.978
Okay, let's take a look
at second and first place.

00:00:12.779 --> 00:00:14.481
Ready, go!

00:00:14.548 --> 00:00:15.749
DEBUT SINGLE RANKING TOP 10

00:00:22.756 --> 00:00:24.124
Why are we second?

00:00:26.260 --> 00:00:27.861
We worked so hard for it.

00:00:28.262 --> 00:00:30.297
It's the agency's power in the end?

00:00:30.364 --> 00:00:34.067
But... it's impressive
to get second place.

00:00:34.134 --> 00:00:35.602
I mean, it's second place!

00:00:35.669 --> 00:00:38.338
That's right!
You guys have worked very hard.

00:00:38.639 --> 00:00:39.873
Isn't second place good enough?

00:00:39.940 --> 00:00:41.241
That's right.

00:00:41.308 --> 00:00:45.012
We didn't even know
if we could debut until recently.

00:00:45.646 --> 00:00:47.047
Yes, indeed.

00:00:47.114 --> 00:00:49.616
Let's get first place next time!

00:00:49.683 --> 00:00:50.951
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:00:55.088 --> 00:00:56.123
What?

00:00:56.189 --> 00:00:57.357
What are you doing, Younki?

00:00:57.424 --> 00:00:58.425
It's impossible!

00:00:59.192 --> 00:01:02.229
The survival rate of groups
that can't get first place in debut

00:01:02.296 --> 00:01:03.964
is only 18%!

00:01:04.031 --> 00:01:06.199
So we can't survive
unless we're first place.

00:01:06.767 --> 00:01:08.869
That's what you said, right? Ms. Nam.

00:01:09.236 --> 00:01:11.505
- Well--
- You're wrong, Younki!

00:01:11.572 --> 00:01:13.373
It's over if you give up.

00:01:18.745 --> 00:01:22.015
It's been streamed and downloaded
many times too, Ms. Nam.

00:01:22.082 --> 00:01:23.216
No way!

00:01:23.283 --> 00:01:24.518
Oh my gosh!

00:01:24.585 --> 00:01:26.286
I'll finally earn some cash?

00:01:26.353 --> 00:01:29.423
The debut song is awesome, after all.

00:01:29.489 --> 00:01:32.159
I'm sure the number is going to rise!

00:01:32.225 --> 00:01:33.493
Right, Mr. Azuma?

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:34.761
Well, who knows?

00:01:34.828 --> 00:01:35.862
Don't say that!

00:01:36.396 --> 00:01:38.765
We're trying to cheer them up!

00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:42.636
I'm the producer, it's my fault
that you couldn't win.

00:01:43.437 --> 00:01:44.538
I am sorry.

00:01:52.746 --> 00:01:53.747
SUMMARY OF K-POP ARTISTS
RESULTS ANALYSIS

00:01:53.814 --> 00:01:57.150
Streaming, CD sales,
appearance on shows...

00:01:57.217 --> 00:02:00.754
You recorded data of various groups
in so much detail.

00:02:00.821 --> 00:02:04.157
An enormous number
of K-pop groups debut every year.

00:02:04.825 --> 00:02:07.794
Most of the groups that can't win
in the debut ranking

00:02:07.995 --> 00:02:10.731
get buried as losers,
and disappear within a few years.

00:02:11.431 --> 00:02:12.499
That's the reality.

00:02:14.101 --> 00:02:17.471
We couldn't get first place.
The result is everything.

00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:21.241
Things like how much effort we put in
aren't evaluated at all.

00:02:21.942 --> 00:02:23.243
That's mean...

00:02:23.310 --> 00:02:25.712
We live in that kind of world.

00:02:28.382 --> 00:02:30.951
If you don't want
to waste your life as a loser

00:02:31.018 --> 00:02:33.220
you can also choose a different path.

00:02:33.286 --> 00:02:34.488
This is something

00:02:35.622 --> 00:02:37.424
that only you can decide.

00:02:44.598 --> 00:02:46.533
I need to do something.

00:02:47.434 --> 00:02:51.238
I thought we had a chance
to get first place.

00:02:54.741 --> 00:02:56.176
It wasn't easy.

00:02:57.344 --> 00:02:59.246
Guys, what do we do now?

00:02:59.980 --> 00:03:04.051
We'll just keep working hard together
to get first place next time, right?

00:03:04.951 --> 00:03:07.054
- Yes, that's all we can do.
- I'll do my best!

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:08.989
- Let's do our best!
- I want to say that...

00:03:09.556 --> 00:03:11.258
but what if, like Mr. Azuma said

00:03:11.324 --> 00:03:14.895
we're buried before we can beat
TORINNER and the other groups?

00:03:15.862 --> 00:03:17.330
Is it worth continuing like this?

00:03:17.397 --> 00:03:18.598
What are you talking about?

00:03:19.166 --> 00:03:20.801
Motivation, energy, Moriwaki.

00:03:20.934 --> 00:03:22.569
We can do anything with that energy.

00:03:22.669 --> 00:03:23.904
Let's get fired up!

00:03:25.205 --> 00:03:27.174
Where did you learn that?

00:03:28.408 --> 00:03:30.043
Oh! TORINNER!

00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:32.012
- What? TORINNER?
- Nice to meet you.

00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:36.917
Darn it! These guys are sparkling.

00:03:37.017 --> 00:03:38.652
We won't lose next time!

00:03:38.719 --> 00:03:39.753
Let's get fired up!

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:42.856
One, two, three!

00:03:42.923 --> 00:03:44.124
- Go!
- Whoa!

00:03:44.191 --> 00:03:45.659
- What's this?
- You didn't do it?

00:03:46.026 --> 00:03:48.328
Glad that it got rid
of your hesitation.

00:03:48.395 --> 00:03:50.130
I didn't hesitate from the start.

00:03:50.430 --> 00:03:51.898
Sorry...

00:03:52.265 --> 00:03:54.101
Congratulations
on getting first place!

00:03:54.568 --> 00:03:56.002
We must thank our fans for it.

00:03:56.069 --> 00:03:58.538
We're so happy
that we can't put it into words.

00:03:58.605 --> 00:03:59.740
Thank you.

00:03:59.806 --> 00:04:01.108
Thanks to your support, Mr. Choi

00:04:01.174 --> 00:04:03.710
we got first place
in the debut ranking as planned.

00:04:03.777 --> 00:04:05.679
The promotion expenses
was more than expected

00:04:05.746 --> 00:04:08.615
but the result and the ability
to achieve that are more important.

00:04:09.316 --> 00:04:10.383
Thank you.

00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:12.853
I'm grateful to hear those words--

00:04:13.487 --> 00:04:15.055
It's not a compliment.

00:04:16.156 --> 00:04:17.190
Not at all.

00:04:19.926 --> 00:04:21.027
I'm worried.

00:04:21.628 --> 00:04:23.396
We spent so much money

00:04:24.164 --> 00:04:27.134
but we only sold 100,000 more copies
than NAZE.

00:04:27.834 --> 00:04:28.869
To think logically

00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:31.905
I can only doubt the ability
of the person in charge.

00:04:35.642 --> 00:04:36.910
I am sorry.

00:04:37.043 --> 00:04:40.547
I entrusted you with our
group's fund, brand and power.

00:04:41.481 --> 00:04:42.549
Originally

00:04:43.817 --> 00:04:46.119
you aren't supposed to struggle,
let alone losing.

00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:53.293
Prove as soon as possible

00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:56.563
that Producer Azuma and NAZE
are no match for us.

00:04:57.931 --> 00:04:59.633
Certainly, sir.

00:05:06.473 --> 00:05:07.541
Mr. Choi.

00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:13.313
Why are you so wary
of Mr. Azuma and NAZE?

00:05:16.049 --> 00:05:17.150
Wary?

00:05:23.256 --> 00:05:24.391
I'm offended.

00:05:29.596 --> 00:05:30.597
I just

00:05:31.765 --> 00:05:34.534
want to train TORINNER
to become absolute artists.

00:05:59.993 --> 00:06:02.662
KOREA LINKS WORLD

00:06:09.135 --> 00:06:10.136
Excuse me.

00:06:10.203 --> 00:06:12.539
Yamada!
Check with the client at once.

00:06:12.973 --> 00:06:15.375
Why don't you ever do anything
unless I tell you to?

00:06:15.442 --> 00:06:18.979
But you told me
to wait for the client's reply.

00:06:19.045 --> 00:06:22.749
Can you take responsibility
if another company gets the job?

00:06:22.816 --> 00:06:25.085
Don't talk back. Do as you're told!

00:06:25.719 --> 00:06:27.187
Move! Move!

00:06:33.860 --> 00:06:34.861
Come in.

00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:41.635
What's your debut's result?

00:06:44.905 --> 00:06:46.406
You're wasting your time.

00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:49.209
I said you couldn't be an idol,
didn't I?

00:06:49.809 --> 00:06:52.045
I'm sorry, Dad.

00:06:55.515 --> 00:06:58.351
Our next live performance is set.

00:06:58.418 --> 00:07:00.720
- Yay!
- Yay!

00:07:00.787 --> 00:07:04.124
The venue will be
a large commercial facility

00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:06.026
called Lake Town.

00:07:06.092 --> 00:07:08.828
Well, it isn't a so-called live venue

00:07:08.895 --> 00:07:12.265
but it's a chance to appeal
to people who don't know NAZE yet

00:07:12.332 --> 00:07:13.366
so let's do our best!

00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:15.368
- Yes, ma'am!
- Yes, ma'am!

00:07:19.039 --> 00:07:21.441
Okay, let's start our lesson now.

00:07:21.508 --> 00:07:22.542
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:07:22.609 --> 00:07:23.710
Let's begin!

00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.211
- Looking forward!
- Looking forward!

00:07:25.879 --> 00:07:28.181
Looks like
they've regained some motivation.

00:07:28.248 --> 00:07:30.150
I need them to earn money.

00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:32.352
I hope you're right.

00:07:33.954 --> 00:07:36.289
TGC PERFORMANCE,
PERFORMANCE AT TORINNER'S CONCERT

00:07:43.697 --> 00:07:45.198
I'd like to talk to you.

00:07:57.177 --> 00:07:59.346
After I opened the Japan branch

00:07:59.412 --> 00:08:01.414
I signed a big contract right away.

00:08:02.382 --> 00:08:05.085
But the Japanese employees
work too slowly

00:08:05.151 --> 00:08:07.253
I just can't trust them.

00:08:08.855 --> 00:08:11.291
Younki, you'll take over
my company someday

00:08:11.691 --> 00:08:13.460
so you'll help in Japan
for the time being.

00:08:14.828 --> 00:08:15.962
Yes.

00:08:16.029 --> 00:08:19.432
My lawyer will cancel your contract
with your agency for you.

00:08:21.267 --> 00:08:24.704
Our next performance has been set.
Let me stay till--

00:08:24.771 --> 00:08:25.972
No!

00:08:26.039 --> 00:08:27.874
How long are you going
to waste your life?

00:08:27.941 --> 00:08:31.044
Even if you're gone,
many people can replace you.

00:08:31.945 --> 00:08:34.547
Think about your future instead.

00:08:36.082 --> 00:08:37.217
I'm sorry

00:08:38.451 --> 00:08:39.552
but...

00:08:40.487 --> 00:08:41.955
this will be the last time.

00:08:45.658 --> 00:08:47.027
It's the absolute last time.

00:08:52.799 --> 00:08:54.300
Hello, everyone.

00:09:04.844 --> 00:09:07.647
- Welcome back, Younki.
- I'm back.

00:09:07.714 --> 00:09:10.383
I made my Minase Hot Pot today.

00:09:10.450 --> 00:09:12.919
You need something nutritious
for your live show.

00:09:12.986 --> 00:09:14.287
- Yay!
- Yay!

00:09:14.354 --> 00:09:16.289
It's the usual Yaminabe, right?

00:09:16.356 --> 00:09:18.725
Don't lump it together
with that mysterious stuff.

00:09:21.394 --> 00:09:23.263
- The meat is huge!
- There's crab too!

00:09:23.396 --> 00:09:24.397
Luxurious!

00:09:24.464 --> 00:09:26.800
But Minase, have you cooked before?

00:09:28.701 --> 00:09:32.939
As long as the ingredients are good,
the dish usually turns out tasty.

00:09:33.006 --> 00:09:36.209
Just for today, I'll show you
the power of an adult's wealth.

00:09:36.276 --> 00:09:38.111
- Wow.
- Wow.

00:09:47.620 --> 00:09:48.755
Eww!

00:09:49.389 --> 00:09:50.623
It's awful?

00:09:51.524 --> 00:09:54.694
Why? I didn't put anything bad in it

00:09:54.961 --> 00:09:56.896
why does it taste so disgusting?

00:09:58.298 --> 00:10:01.935
That's what you call "talent"
in Japanese.

00:10:02.001 --> 00:10:03.636
- Wow!
- That's harsh!

00:10:03.703 --> 00:10:05.905
How frustrating!

00:10:05.972 --> 00:10:08.074
Once more! I'll make it again!

00:10:08.141 --> 00:10:10.310
No, no! We'll eat it together.

00:10:10.376 --> 00:10:12.312
We're friends

00:10:12.378 --> 00:10:15.081
so we share the hard times
and the difficult times together.

00:10:15.248 --> 00:10:17.817
Don't make my cooking
sound like some kind of training.

00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:21.888
- You'll eat it?
- Let's try it. Go on!

00:10:21.955 --> 00:10:25.058
Minase is absent-minded sometimes

00:10:25.592 --> 00:10:27.494
but she's always on our side.

00:10:28.394 --> 00:10:29.796
She roots for us.

00:10:31.397 --> 00:10:34.000
- Me too! Me too!
- What? Really?

00:10:35.368 --> 00:10:37.837
- What? What?
- I can't eat anymore!

00:10:37.904 --> 00:10:40.707
When I felt anxious,
and when I felt frustrated

00:10:40.773 --> 00:10:44.144
these members were always by my side

00:10:44.210 --> 00:10:45.545
that's why I could overcome it.

00:10:46.446 --> 00:10:48.481
- I'll work on the flavor.
- That's genius.

00:10:50.583 --> 00:10:52.719
It's awful! This tastes awful.

00:10:52.785 --> 00:10:53.920
But...

00:10:55.955 --> 00:10:57.056
I want some too!

00:10:57.123 --> 00:10:58.825
- What?
- He's here!

00:10:58.892 --> 00:11:00.160
It's absolutely delicious.

00:11:00.226 --> 00:11:01.761
- Try it.
- What do you think?

00:11:02.529 --> 00:11:03.630
Disgusting!

00:11:03.863 --> 00:11:05.265
This is really bad!

00:11:05.431 --> 00:11:06.666
It's over.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:09.569
I said you couldn't be an idol,
didn't I?

00:11:09.669 --> 00:11:11.304
How long are you going
to waste your life?

00:11:11.371 --> 00:11:14.340
Even if you're gone,
many people can replace you.

00:11:18.611 --> 00:11:21.848
It was an impossible dream
for me anyway.

00:11:25.752 --> 00:11:27.353
SEVERAL DAYS LATER

00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:30.356
NAZE. It's a weird name.
Do you know it?

00:11:30.423 --> 00:11:32.825
I've seen them.
Isn't it a K-pop group?

00:11:32.892 --> 00:11:34.961
Oh, the disappointing kids.

00:11:35.028 --> 00:11:36.930
The losers who failed the audition.

00:11:36.996 --> 00:11:38.698
Yes, that's them.

00:11:38.765 --> 00:11:40.767
Is this where we'll do
the live performance?

00:11:40.833 --> 00:11:42.802
Will anybody be watching?

00:11:42.869 --> 00:11:46.506
You guys! Stop complaining.
Hurry and get ready.

00:11:46.573 --> 00:11:47.840
- Yes...
- Yes...

00:11:47.907 --> 00:11:50.243
I can't really get motivated.

00:11:50.310 --> 00:11:52.946
It feels like we're
interrupting people shopping.

00:11:55.114 --> 00:11:58.418
No matter where it is,
if we give our best performance

00:11:58.484 --> 00:12:00.587
someone will surely be watching.

00:12:00.653 --> 00:12:02.555
Right, guys?

00:12:03.256 --> 00:12:04.257
Let's do our best.

00:12:04.324 --> 00:12:06.059
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

00:12:07.093 --> 00:12:08.261
This will be the last time.

00:12:09.596 --> 00:12:11.397
Let's stand by.

00:12:11.464 --> 00:12:12.465
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:12:12.532 --> 00:12:15.201
Younki, let's huddle.

00:12:15.268 --> 00:12:16.436
- Let's go!
- Come on!

00:12:16.502 --> 00:12:17.971
(Korean)

00:12:18.037 --> 00:12:19.405
- Let's do our best.
- Yeah.

00:12:21.541 --> 00:12:25.912
It's always been my dream
to perform on stage.

00:12:30.350 --> 00:12:32.785
Let's give it our all! Let's go!

00:12:34.087 --> 00:12:35.188
One, two...

00:12:35.788 --> 00:12:36.923
- NAZE!
- NAZE!

00:12:37.257 --> 00:12:38.858
- Yes!
- Let's do our best today!

00:12:38.925 --> 00:12:39.926
Let's have fun!

00:12:39.993 --> 00:12:41.894
Is it just me,
or is it different from usual?

00:12:42.929 --> 00:12:43.963
Yeah.

00:12:46.566 --> 00:12:47.967
LAKE TOWN HAPPY WINTER FESTA

00:13:16.829 --> 00:13:18.564
It's not great.

00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:21.200
I guess they really are losers.

00:13:21.267 --> 00:13:22.635
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

00:13:25.171 --> 00:13:26.406
I knew it'd turn out like this.

00:13:26.472 --> 00:13:28.074
They don't want to watch.

00:13:30.843 --> 00:13:32.145
What were you thinking?

00:13:32.211 --> 00:13:34.280
What was that performance today?

00:13:34.347 --> 00:13:37.183
Your movements were dull, the moves
were wrong, and you zoned out.

00:13:37.684 --> 00:13:39.218
I am sorry.

00:13:39.285 --> 00:13:42.088
You shouldn't perform in front
of people with that quality.

00:13:42.155 --> 00:13:44.891
This is your job! Do you get it?

00:13:45.291 --> 00:13:47.960
But nobody was watching.

00:13:48.027 --> 00:13:50.396
We know it's our job,
but in that environment...

00:13:50.463 --> 00:13:52.265
I'm quitting NAZE today.

00:13:55.868 --> 00:13:57.737
Why are you quitting
all of a sudden, Younki?

00:13:59.739 --> 00:14:02.442
We can't beat TORINNER
because you're like this.

00:14:03.443 --> 00:14:07.046
A bunch of talentless losers
can't win if they slack off!

00:14:07.113 --> 00:14:08.147
What?

00:14:08.514 --> 00:14:10.783
- Wait! Stop...
- Wait, you two!

00:14:11.351 --> 00:14:14.153
Younki, why are you quitting?
Did something happen?

00:14:15.188 --> 00:14:18.791
I can't survive
in a team of trashy members.

00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.193
There's no future.

00:14:21.494 --> 00:14:23.996
I'm saying you can't afford
to fool around anymore!

00:14:24.063 --> 00:14:25.832
Trashy? Fooling around?

00:14:25.898 --> 00:14:27.934
- Guys! Guys, stop!
- Stop!

00:14:28.134 --> 00:14:29.202
Azuma, stop them!

00:14:29.268 --> 00:14:31.204
Stop it!

00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:34.040
Are you going to abandon your friends
and run away?

00:14:35.375 --> 00:14:39.879
It doesn't matter
even if I'm gone anyway, right?

00:14:40.179 --> 00:14:42.215
We said we'd make our dream
come true together!

00:14:42.281 --> 00:14:44.417
Stop being naive and stop dreaming!

00:14:45.752 --> 00:14:49.422
Be careful. I don't want you
to injure our members' faces.

00:15:09.509 --> 00:15:11.144
ATO

00:15:13.012 --> 00:15:14.180
ATO

00:15:22.088 --> 00:15:24.357
Sorry, everyone.

00:15:27.994 --> 00:15:29.262
It's done!

00:15:29.328 --> 00:15:31.330
Motivation, energy, bean sprouts!

00:15:31.397 --> 00:15:32.532
Eat when it's still warm.

00:15:33.099 --> 00:15:35.701
Younki isn't back yet, is he?

00:15:36.235 --> 00:15:38.471
No, he didn't answer my calls either.

00:15:39.472 --> 00:15:40.973
Just ignore him.

00:15:41.507 --> 00:15:42.775
He really let me down.

00:15:43.576 --> 00:15:45.611
He's just a rich kid, after all.

00:15:45.678 --> 00:15:47.413
Younki is rich?

00:15:47.480 --> 00:15:51.350
His dad is the president
of a trading company.

00:15:52.318 --> 00:15:55.755
It has branches in the US,
and it opened one in Japan recently.

00:15:56.022 --> 00:15:59.559
In the end, K-pop was a game to him.

00:16:00.960 --> 00:16:02.895
We're betting our lives on it.

00:16:03.196 --> 00:16:04.397
This is ridiculous!

00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:11.304
Okay, let's dig in!

00:16:11.370 --> 00:16:12.872
Let's dig in!

00:16:12.939 --> 00:16:14.240
Looks delicious.

00:16:14.440 --> 00:16:15.842
Let's eat.

00:16:18.277 --> 00:16:20.346
- Delicious, Dohyeok!
- Right?

00:16:20.413 --> 00:16:21.914
I'm full of motivation and energy!

00:16:21.981 --> 00:16:23.015
There's no meat.

00:16:23.082 --> 00:16:26.085
Only honest people can see the meat.

00:16:26.152 --> 00:16:27.153
What's that?

00:16:27.220 --> 00:16:29.288
So, Kaisei, you can't see it.

00:16:29.355 --> 00:16:30.923
Wait, I surely can!

00:16:32.124 --> 00:16:34.026
Oh, found some meat!

00:16:42.168 --> 00:16:43.636
You work too slowly!

00:16:44.370 --> 00:16:47.206
I'm not leaving anything to someone
incompetent like you anymore.

00:16:47.740 --> 00:16:49.342
I'll do everything myself.

00:16:49.509 --> 00:16:50.676
You're fired!

00:16:57.183 --> 00:16:58.885
Attend the meeting with me tomorrow.

00:16:59.085 --> 00:17:01.687
Before that,
your hair color is a disgrace.

00:17:02.221 --> 00:17:03.623
Dye it black at once.

00:17:04.790 --> 00:17:05.825
Yes, Dad.

00:17:07.793 --> 00:17:10.663
It seems the member, Younki,
is quitting.

00:17:12.465 --> 00:17:16.903
Indeed. Idols from a small agency

00:17:16.969 --> 00:17:20.006
have no future potential
and no stability.

00:17:20.072 --> 00:17:27.046
I reckon the other members
will follow suit and quit.

00:17:33.152 --> 00:17:34.153
Thanks.

00:17:35.121 --> 00:17:37.790
NAZE is going to fall apart
very soon.

00:17:37.857 --> 00:17:40.760
I will proceed
to undermine the other members.

00:17:41.427 --> 00:17:42.762
The flies are annoying.

00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:44.997
Please get rid of them quickly.

00:17:46.332 --> 00:17:47.466
Certainly, sir.

00:18:08.654 --> 00:18:11.624
Younki hasn't come back.

00:18:27.373 --> 00:18:29.375
He cried at that time, didn't he?

00:18:30.476 --> 00:18:31.477
Yes.

00:18:32.378 --> 00:18:36.282
Maybe he didn't really want to quit.

00:18:37.583 --> 00:18:40.519
He's weirdly serious.

00:18:42.488 --> 00:18:43.756
He's difficult.

00:18:44.090 --> 00:18:45.992
If someone says he's at his limit

00:18:46.058 --> 00:18:48.894
he would suddenly work harder,
even if he's also exhausted.

00:18:48.961 --> 00:18:50.896
His competitive streak is no joke.

00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:52.798
Even though he has a good upbringing.

00:18:52.865 --> 00:18:53.966
But...

00:18:54.667 --> 00:18:57.403
He said his childhood was tough.

00:18:57.703 --> 00:19:01.674
He said his dad was always working
and never home.

00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:05.011
He said
they had never talked properly alone.

00:19:05.678 --> 00:19:07.279
He must have been lonely.

00:19:08.147 --> 00:19:11.617
But in the end, he's going
to take over his dad's company.

00:19:11.684 --> 00:19:13.853
Safer than being an idol.

00:19:13.919 --> 00:19:17.490
You mean
Younki's decision wasn't wrong?

00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:21.961
Yeah, I guess so.

00:19:23.462 --> 00:19:26.332
Then, do you mean we all...

00:19:27.233 --> 00:19:29.001
made the wrong decision
for our lives?

00:19:30.703 --> 00:19:32.505
I guess so.

00:19:40.012 --> 00:19:41.347
Is that so?

00:19:42.048 --> 00:19:43.416
Is it really so?

00:19:45.985 --> 00:19:47.453
We need money.

00:19:49.021 --> 00:19:50.089
True.

00:19:50.656 --> 00:19:53.459
But it isn't everything, is it?

00:19:55.461 --> 00:19:56.495
Yeah.

00:19:58.497 --> 00:19:59.765
What is it, then?

00:20:01.467 --> 00:20:02.568
I wonder.

00:20:03.135 --> 00:20:04.270
I wonder.

00:20:05.538 --> 00:20:07.206
You guys, go to sleep.

00:20:14.580 --> 00:20:17.349
Mr. Azuma, is Younki
really not coming back?

00:20:18.784 --> 00:20:22.755
I still want to pursue our dream
with Younki.

00:20:28.427 --> 00:20:30.162
You guys are such a pain.

00:20:31.630 --> 00:20:32.898
In the past

00:20:33.566 --> 00:20:35.868
his dad said he wouldn't be able
to become an idol

00:20:35.935 --> 00:20:37.737
so he should go to university.

00:20:37.803 --> 00:20:39.905
His dad was strongly against it.

00:20:41.207 --> 00:20:45.244
At that time, he said he'd become
an artist who can get first place

00:20:45.311 --> 00:20:48.047
and he'd give up his dream at once
if he couldn't do it.

00:20:48.114 --> 00:20:49.548
He promised his dad that.

00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:53.586
He made a promise like that?

00:20:53.652 --> 00:20:56.789
That means,
he didn't want us to be sad

00:20:57.289 --> 00:20:59.091
so he said something
to make us angry.

00:20:59.825 --> 00:21:01.060
He's childish.

00:21:01.994 --> 00:21:04.130
That's so like our stubborn Younki.

00:21:12.805 --> 00:21:14.340
I've seen this face somewhere.

00:21:16.475 --> 00:21:17.643
Thank you.

00:21:17.710 --> 00:21:21.247
We'll certainly deliver
the goods tomorrow.

00:21:21.313 --> 00:21:22.481
Thank you.

00:21:26.819 --> 00:21:30.856
It makes me jealous
that you have a fine heir like this.

00:21:30.923 --> 00:21:33.592
Not at all. My son isn't reliable.

00:21:33.659 --> 00:21:34.660
You're too modest.

00:21:34.727 --> 00:21:36.128
Look forward to working with you.

00:21:43.235 --> 00:21:44.303
Oh?

00:21:47.139 --> 00:21:49.775
Mr. Yamada,
where are the other employees?

00:21:53.546 --> 00:21:54.680
No idea.

00:22:02.688 --> 00:22:06.091
The Japanese market will become
a mainstay of our business.

00:22:06.458 --> 00:22:09.195
That's why I invested in it
despite the big risk.

00:22:09.962 --> 00:22:10.963
Yes.

00:22:11.030 --> 00:22:13.165
We'll expand the range
of new products

00:22:13.232 --> 00:22:15.234
to make people's lives abundant.

00:22:15.734 --> 00:22:18.170
Totally different from
the half-hearted work of idols.

00:22:18.537 --> 00:22:19.905
It's worthy and meaningful.

00:22:22.541 --> 00:22:24.143
What? Got a problem?

00:22:25.411 --> 00:22:26.412
No.

00:22:26.478 --> 00:22:28.080
Entertainment isn't something

00:22:28.347 --> 00:22:31.183
people can't live without
in the world.

00:22:31.250 --> 00:22:34.687
Let the uneducated dropouts
and weirdos take care of it.

00:22:34.753 --> 00:22:36.989
If you don't want to fail in life,
do as I say.

00:22:38.357 --> 00:22:39.358
Yes, Dad.

00:22:40.459 --> 00:22:42.027
When we deliver these tomorrow

00:22:42.094 --> 00:22:43.629
our products will be on the shelves

00:22:43.696 --> 00:22:45.865
of convenience stores
and supermarkets in Japan.

00:22:45.931 --> 00:22:46.932
Isn't it impressive?

00:22:46.999 --> 00:22:50.002
All of these?
It'll need a lot of manpower.

00:22:50.936 --> 00:22:52.338
Will the employees come tomorrow?

00:22:54.373 --> 00:22:55.374
Why do you ask?

00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:58.744
There was no one in the office
just now.

00:23:00.813 --> 00:23:03.549
I fired all the Japanese employees.

00:23:03.616 --> 00:23:06.051
They work too slowly,
and I can't trust them.

00:23:06.252 --> 00:23:08.053
What?
Then who will deliver the goods?

00:23:09.221 --> 00:23:13.125
I've introduced the latest machine
and automized everything.

00:23:13.192 --> 00:23:16.362
Therefore, I don't need any help
from the employees.

00:23:17.062 --> 00:23:19.431
Rather than playing nice
to untrustworthy people

00:23:20.165 --> 00:23:21.600
it's better to do it alone.

00:23:26.338 --> 00:23:27.573
Better to be alone...

00:23:32.177 --> 00:23:34.280
Hey, future big-shot CEO.

00:23:34.713 --> 00:23:35.915
What? Mr. Azuma!

00:23:35.981 --> 00:23:37.316
What are you here for?

00:23:37.883 --> 00:23:40.886
You didn't take your things with you.
There you go.

00:23:41.186 --> 00:23:43.289
Sorry for the trouble.

00:23:44.256 --> 00:23:45.357
You look cool.

00:23:45.791 --> 00:23:49.428
Is the CEO training tough?
Your dad's company is on a roll, huh?

00:23:51.931 --> 00:23:55.301
He closed a big deal,
and he looks happy.

00:23:55.834 --> 00:23:57.403
You talk like it's not your business.

00:23:59.872 --> 00:24:02.775
He's always been like this.
How should I put it?

00:24:03.909 --> 00:24:06.478
He's someone who trusts only himself.

00:24:07.179 --> 00:24:12.551
He doesn't care about how
I or other people feel at all.

00:24:13.686 --> 00:24:14.887
That hits a sore spot.

00:24:14.954 --> 00:24:16.288
You aren't like that!

00:24:17.723 --> 00:24:21.226
Indeed, you're bossy, arrogant,
and you think you're the best.

00:24:21.293 --> 00:24:22.795
That spot is very sore.

00:24:24.863 --> 00:24:25.931
But...

00:24:26.532 --> 00:24:29.201
you actually see us.

00:24:30.469 --> 00:24:31.603
You...

00:24:32.838 --> 00:24:36.875
You do like us, and we can tell.

00:24:39.511 --> 00:24:40.980
You're different from my dad.

00:24:42.548 --> 00:24:44.583
It's tough to have a great dad.

00:24:48.087 --> 00:24:49.188
I...

00:24:50.889 --> 00:24:54.560
The other day, when you said to me,
"Don't hurt our members..."

00:24:54.626 --> 00:24:55.828
Be careful.

00:24:55.894 --> 00:24:58.297
I don't want you
to injure our members' faces.

00:24:59.098 --> 00:25:00.499
You said "our."

00:25:01.567 --> 00:25:02.801
It felt like

00:25:04.003 --> 00:25:06.238
you said I wasn't one of you anymore.

00:25:07.239 --> 00:25:08.507
And that...

00:25:08.974 --> 00:25:11.176
That made me incredibly sad.

00:25:14.179 --> 00:25:18.617
I thought, "I'll never be able
to see them again."

00:25:20.652 --> 00:25:23.922
But I can't say I want to go back now

00:25:24.556 --> 00:25:28.293
and all my dad thinks about
is his company.

00:25:30.996 --> 00:25:32.097
I...

00:25:34.333 --> 00:25:36.835
I don't belong anywhere now.

00:25:39.738 --> 00:25:41.874
Nobody wants me anymore.

00:25:43.776 --> 00:25:45.778
When I think that, I just...

00:25:50.582 --> 00:25:52.985
You two are messed up
in all kinds of ways.

00:25:56.155 --> 00:25:58.390
Is your dad here now?

00:26:02.327 --> 00:26:06.432
I've left the contract cancellation
with your agency to the lawyer.

00:26:06.498 --> 00:26:08.667
I don't think
we have anything else to talk about.

00:26:09.268 --> 00:26:10.569
Actually, I came here

00:26:10.636 --> 00:26:15.040
to ask if you might give us
another chance to take Younki back.

00:26:15.107 --> 00:26:18.410
Younki? You want me
to let him go back to the idol group?

00:26:19.678 --> 00:26:21.180
Impossible.

00:26:22.314 --> 00:26:23.949
I'm sorry, but please leave.

00:26:24.016 --> 00:26:25.851
Younki's dad, your dad

00:26:25.918 --> 00:26:28.754
that is his granddad,
was also a singer, right?

00:26:30.089 --> 00:26:31.090
What about that?

00:26:31.156 --> 00:26:32.157
I just thought

00:26:32.224 --> 00:26:35.227
it was wonderful how things get
passed down from parent to child.

00:26:37.563 --> 00:26:40.732
My dad and Younki have never met.

00:26:41.266 --> 00:26:44.536
He's a stranger now,
so please stop meddling.

00:26:44.603 --> 00:26:46.772
No, it's not about Younki.

00:26:46.839 --> 00:26:51.210
I just thought you must also like
songs and performances.

00:26:51.276 --> 00:26:54.046
Me? I'm not interested--

00:26:54.113 --> 00:26:55.481
You came...

00:26:56.315 --> 00:26:59.118
to NAZE's every live show,
didn't you?

00:27:01.987 --> 00:27:05.357
During live shows, I tend to watch
the audience more than the stage.

00:27:05.724 --> 00:27:08.327
Gender, age, what they're wearing...

00:27:08.393 --> 00:27:10.329
It's very good marketing.

00:27:11.997 --> 00:27:15.534
That's why when I found your photo
on the Internet

00:27:16.135 --> 00:27:20.072
I thought I had seen this face
somewhere.

00:27:25.344 --> 00:27:27.112
You've been rooting for us

00:27:27.212 --> 00:27:30.649
I'm sorry that we couldn't get
first place in the debut ranking.

00:27:33.585 --> 00:27:35.721
I can't believe you know that much.

00:27:38.624 --> 00:27:40.993
I hated my dad.

00:27:43.095 --> 00:27:45.330
It's true that he was a singer

00:27:45.397 --> 00:27:47.533
but he never came home,
never sent money

00:27:47.599 --> 00:27:49.768
and neglected our family.

00:27:50.602 --> 00:27:54.873
That's why I swore I would never be
a parent like my dad.

00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:58.810
No matter what I do,
no matter what others think

00:27:58.877 --> 00:28:02.915
I just have to make sure
my family had enough to eat.

00:28:03.649 --> 00:28:05.184
That alone was my ego.

00:28:08.887 --> 00:28:11.323
When Younki said
he wanted to become an idol

00:28:11.390 --> 00:28:13.525
my dad came to mind.

00:28:14.092 --> 00:28:17.362
I absolutely don't want Younki
to become someone like him

00:28:17.429 --> 00:28:19.531
so I said
he'd never be able to make it!

00:28:21.433 --> 00:28:24.036
I said horrible things deliberately.

00:28:25.337 --> 00:28:29.474
Even now, I still haven't forgotten
the words I said to him.

00:28:31.310 --> 00:28:34.613
That's why I think Younki hates me.

00:28:35.314 --> 00:28:38.050
But I do not regret it.

00:28:38.717 --> 00:28:40.919
There are things
you don't realize when you're young.

00:28:41.553 --> 00:28:45.958
You'll suffer
if you make a wrong choice in life.

00:28:46.525 --> 00:28:49.328
Even if he hates me,
even if he resents me

00:28:50.195 --> 00:28:54.166
it's the parent's responsibility
to protect his child's future.

00:29:03.442 --> 00:29:07.212
I will not allow my son
to return to the group.

00:29:08.480 --> 00:29:11.883
I want Younki to have a stable life.

00:29:12.651 --> 00:29:13.919
That is why

00:29:13.986 --> 00:29:17.456
I've worked desperately
to make this company grow.

00:29:32.671 --> 00:29:34.039
He's a good dad.

00:29:38.510 --> 00:29:43.081
I had no idea that he had come
to watch our live performances.

00:29:44.182 --> 00:29:47.019
He just loves you very much.

00:29:49.454 --> 00:29:53.158
He should have just told me
what he thought.

00:29:54.726 --> 00:29:58.463
You're so stubborn.
Like father, like son.

00:30:00.799 --> 00:30:01.900
That's true.

00:30:07.439 --> 00:30:09.341
I talked to Younki's dad

00:30:09.508 --> 00:30:11.643
but he can't come back to NAZE.

00:30:13.979 --> 00:30:15.047
But I thought

00:30:15.113 --> 00:30:19.718
Younki's dad came to the conclusion
because he loved Younki.

00:30:23.422 --> 00:30:26.692
It's no use thinking about it!
Let's forget about Younki!

00:30:26.758 --> 00:30:28.427
Let's do a huddle,
with me in the center!

00:30:28.493 --> 00:30:30.495
Hey, read the room!

00:30:30.962 --> 00:30:32.998
You sure know
some old-fashioned words.

00:30:36.868 --> 00:30:37.903
Well...

00:30:38.770 --> 00:30:39.971
Mr. Azuma...

00:30:55.187 --> 00:30:57.856
THE NEXT DAY

00:30:59.191 --> 00:31:01.526
What's this? What's going on?

00:31:07.132 --> 00:31:08.900
Why aren't they moving? Darn it!

00:31:09.201 --> 00:31:10.736
What's wrong?

00:31:11.737 --> 00:31:13.138
The forklifts are not moving.

00:31:13.505 --> 00:31:16.241
There was no problem
in the trial run yesterday.

00:31:17.209 --> 00:31:19.511
The trucks will arrive at 3 p.m.
We must load the goods

00:31:19.578 --> 00:31:20.746
and leave at 4 p.m.

00:31:21.747 --> 00:31:22.981
Or we'll breach the contract.

00:31:23.281 --> 00:31:25.016
If there's no money
deposited tomorrow

00:31:25.083 --> 00:31:26.585
our company will be over!

00:31:27.352 --> 00:31:29.554
Anyway, let's move them
to the loading dock.

00:31:31.790 --> 00:31:32.791
Hurry up!

00:31:45.837 --> 00:31:47.606
We won't make it in time!

00:31:47.672 --> 00:31:50.175
Which employee is familiar
with the forklifts?

00:31:50.242 --> 00:31:51.676
Yamada, the one who introduced them.

00:32:05.390 --> 00:32:06.558
LIST OF EMPLOYEES

00:32:07.826 --> 00:32:09.227
YAMADA TAKASHI

00:32:16.468 --> 00:32:19.871
I can't get a hold of Mr. Yamada!
What about the other employees?

00:32:21.807 --> 00:32:23.008
Dad!

00:32:24.609 --> 00:32:28.079
The other employees too!
They resent me for firing them.

00:32:28.880 --> 00:32:32.284
An employee must've done this
out of spite.

00:32:32.884 --> 00:32:33.919
What?

00:32:46.164 --> 00:32:47.466
It's over.

00:32:47.666 --> 00:32:52.304
Everything I've built
over these 20 years!

00:33:02.113 --> 00:33:03.582
Which way is this?

00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:16.828
Mr. Yamada!

00:33:19.431 --> 00:33:20.732
It's too late.

00:33:53.164 --> 00:33:54.165
Darn it.

00:34:04.743 --> 00:34:05.777
Why?

00:34:08.413 --> 00:34:11.349
What are you going to do?
We won't make it in time!

00:34:12.684 --> 00:34:13.885
I'm sorry.

00:34:14.886 --> 00:34:16.555
The machines won't start.

00:34:17.355 --> 00:34:18.857
Are you telling us
to drive the trucks empty?

00:34:19.224 --> 00:34:20.792
Do something!

00:34:23.828 --> 00:34:27.532
I am sorry, but please leave.

00:34:33.505 --> 00:34:35.340
We'll carry them!

00:34:38.910 --> 00:34:40.478
We'll load the trucks.

00:34:44.583 --> 00:34:47.152
Huh? You guys will do it
by yourselves?

00:34:47.218 --> 00:34:48.320
No way.

00:34:48.386 --> 00:34:50.589
We'll definitely get it loaded
in time.

00:34:50.655 --> 00:34:51.990
Okay, let's begin!

00:34:52.057 --> 00:34:53.291
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:34:54.593 --> 00:34:57.562
What are you talking about?
The road are congested in the rain!

00:34:57.629 --> 00:35:00.098
We'll be late
if we leave later than 4 p.m.

00:35:00.165 --> 00:35:01.600
- Understand!
- Understand!

00:35:02.133 --> 00:35:06.004
Dad, it's over if you give up!

00:35:06.938 --> 00:35:08.239
Let's do it with them!

00:35:11.977 --> 00:35:13.078
Okay.

00:35:14.379 --> 00:35:15.814
It's heavy!

00:35:16.014 --> 00:35:19.017
Do your best!

00:35:19.484 --> 00:35:21.319
Dad, are you okay?

00:35:21.386 --> 00:35:22.554
Okay. Hurry up!

00:35:23.755 --> 00:35:25.123
You won't make it in time!

00:35:25.590 --> 00:35:26.758
Guys!

00:35:30.362 --> 00:35:32.864
Sorry, coming through.

00:35:33.365 --> 00:35:34.866
(Korean)

00:35:38.203 --> 00:35:40.005
Twenty more minutes.

00:35:45.210 --> 00:35:46.478
We won't make it.

00:35:57.322 --> 00:35:58.390
Yamada?

00:35:59.891 --> 00:36:02.327
Clear the loading area there.

00:36:02.394 --> 00:36:04.963
Let's use the forklifts
to move everything!

00:36:06.698 --> 00:36:08.366
Thank you, Mr. Yamada.

00:36:09.401 --> 00:36:10.502
Hurry up!

00:36:11.002 --> 00:36:12.470
Hurry...

00:36:12.537 --> 00:36:14.072
- Be quick...
- We can do it!

00:36:14.139 --> 00:36:16.207
- Clear the way!
- We can do it!

00:36:16.274 --> 00:36:18.777
But still, that machines are amazing.

00:36:18.843 --> 00:36:21.212
- 15 minutes left!
- Only 15 minutes!

00:36:21.279 --> 00:36:22.814
We'll make it for sure!

00:36:25.884 --> 00:36:29.721
This is cutting it way too close!
But I promise we're going to make it.

00:36:31.089 --> 00:36:32.624
Thank you!

00:36:46.371 --> 00:36:49.641
Yamada, why did you come?

00:36:54.979 --> 00:36:56.247
Because your son...

00:36:57.982 --> 00:37:01.052
was so earnest about it.

00:37:02.587 --> 00:37:03.855
Also...

00:37:07.358 --> 00:37:08.526
This photo...

00:37:12.263 --> 00:37:14.499
You still have it?

00:37:14.566 --> 00:37:16.000
OPENING OF JAPAN BRANCH

00:37:17.469 --> 00:37:20.405
I put it in the employee directory,
so that I wouldn't lose it.

00:37:23.475 --> 00:37:24.809
You think

00:37:26.277 --> 00:37:28.513
we're useless and not trustworthy.

00:37:29.447 --> 00:37:31.015
It's the only way we could see it.

00:37:32.283 --> 00:37:36.521
I suppose someone wanted
to teach you a lesson too.

00:37:38.223 --> 00:37:39.290
Those machines...

00:37:40.992 --> 00:37:45.396
You need a password
to disable the startup process.

00:37:45.997 --> 00:37:47.465
Only we, employees, know that.

00:37:53.271 --> 00:37:54.305
But...

00:37:55.874 --> 00:37:57.509
the messages behind it...

00:37:58.910 --> 00:38:00.712
YAMADA: HIGH COMMUNICATION SKILLS.
ABLE BUSINESSMAN.

00:38:00.779 --> 00:38:04.949
If you could tell us how you feel
like you did in the past

00:38:05.483 --> 00:38:06.484
then we...

00:38:07.352 --> 00:38:09.354
We would be able to work harder.

00:38:11.189 --> 00:38:15.894
We worked with pride too.

00:38:22.133 --> 00:38:23.334
You're right.

00:38:26.137 --> 00:38:27.472
I was wrong.

00:38:29.107 --> 00:38:32.410
And thank you very much
for helping me today.

00:38:36.514 --> 00:38:37.615
President...

00:38:48.126 --> 00:38:49.227
If at that time

00:38:50.395 --> 00:38:52.230
you guys hadn't come

00:38:53.932 --> 00:38:55.533
we wouldn't have made it in time.

00:38:57.368 --> 00:38:58.770
Thank you!

00:39:02.407 --> 00:39:03.675
We just happened

00:39:05.376 --> 00:39:06.911
to have come to give you this.

00:39:07.745 --> 00:39:09.981
TO NAZE'S YOUNKI

00:39:10.048 --> 00:39:12.383
WE'RE FRIENDS. WE LOVE YOU.
WE'RE ALWAYS ON YOUR SIDE!

00:39:12.450 --> 00:39:14.485
We're friends forever.

00:39:17.789 --> 00:39:20.625
We're with you during the hard times
and the difficult times.

00:39:21.893 --> 00:39:23.328
Even when we're apart

00:39:24.963 --> 00:39:26.664
our heart will always be with you.

00:39:36.307 --> 00:39:37.542
Thank you so much.

00:39:39.043 --> 00:39:40.345
Younki, you too.

00:39:41.512 --> 00:39:42.914
You did very well.

00:39:47.151 --> 00:39:48.152
Everyone.

00:39:52.657 --> 00:39:55.894
Thank you very much.

00:39:56.861 --> 00:39:59.998
My son has so many precious friends

00:40:00.064 --> 00:40:03.101
who cherish him so much.

00:40:03.167 --> 00:40:04.769
I had no idea.

00:40:05.536 --> 00:40:07.238
I'm not good enough as a dad.

00:40:08.206 --> 00:40:10.508
Exactly! Younki's dad,
you're arrogant--

00:40:10.575 --> 00:40:11.910
You idiot!

00:40:11.976 --> 00:40:12.977
I'm very sorry!

00:40:13.044 --> 00:40:15.613
No, Kaisei is right.

00:40:15.680 --> 00:40:17.181
What? You know my name?

00:40:17.982 --> 00:40:20.351
Well... yeah.

00:40:25.323 --> 00:40:28.126
Younki's dad,
this is our last request.

00:40:28.927 --> 00:40:33.231
Would you give us one more chance?

00:40:34.532 --> 00:40:36.334
We've been chasing this dream

00:40:37.468 --> 00:40:41.039
we want to do it with Younki.
All seven of us.

00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:43.841
Please think about it!

00:40:44.575 --> 00:40:46.244
- Please think about it!
- Please think about it!

00:40:57.221 --> 00:40:58.222
NAZE...

00:41:02.427 --> 00:41:04.195
couldn't get first place
in the debut ranking.

00:41:05.663 --> 00:41:09.801
Continuing just because it's
your dream, and it's what you like

00:41:10.201 --> 00:41:11.436
is tough and difficult.

00:41:11.502 --> 00:41:13.004
That's the reality.

00:41:17.408 --> 00:41:18.409
But...

00:41:19.110 --> 00:41:21.112
if you open the tough, difficult path

00:41:21.179 --> 00:41:24.415
together with the people you cherish

00:41:25.116 --> 00:41:27.251
maybe you'll be able to grow.

00:41:32.657 --> 00:41:35.626
I'll ask a favor as a dad.

00:41:36.995 --> 00:41:38.229
Will you

00:41:39.664 --> 00:41:42.100
let my son join you again?

00:41:46.938 --> 00:41:48.906
Yay, Younki!

00:41:49.140 --> 00:41:51.175
Yay!

00:41:51.242 --> 00:41:53.244
Thank goodness!

00:42:00.018 --> 00:42:01.919
I'll be responsible
and look after him.

00:42:02.587 --> 00:42:03.654
Please...

00:42:05.556 --> 00:42:07.191
take care of my son.

00:42:11.095 --> 00:42:12.130
Hey!

00:42:16.601 --> 00:42:19.370
Dad, thank you.

00:42:21.639 --> 00:42:24.909
It's going to be tough,
but do eat properly.

00:42:24.976 --> 00:42:28.046
Your mom and I
will always be rooting for you.

00:42:29.147 --> 00:42:30.181
Okay!

00:42:46.397 --> 00:42:48.900
Excuse me. Do you like NAZE?

00:42:49.534 --> 00:42:50.535
Yeah...

00:42:50.601 --> 00:42:52.036
Who's your fave?

00:42:54.806 --> 00:42:57.075
- It's Younki.
- Oh, really?

00:42:57.141 --> 00:42:58.943
- Me too!
- He's my fave too!

00:42:59.010 --> 00:43:00.144
We're the same!

00:43:00.211 --> 00:43:02.046
Younki's smile is the best, right?

00:43:02.113 --> 00:43:03.114
Yes!

00:43:08.886 --> 00:43:10.721
Do your best. Go for it!

00:43:16.027 --> 00:43:17.195
Hey.

00:43:17.261 --> 00:43:18.996
Answer your phone!

00:43:19.063 --> 00:43:20.398
It's serious!

00:43:20.465 --> 00:43:21.499
Serious?

00:43:21.566 --> 00:43:22.667
Ow!

00:43:22.733 --> 00:43:23.768
That!

00:43:26.537 --> 00:43:28.773
Ji-soo? What's the matter?

00:43:33.344 --> 00:43:34.345
Will you

00:43:35.546 --> 00:43:37.381
let me join this agency?

00:43:41.085 --> 00:43:43.788
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

00:43:43.855 --> 00:43:45.189
What've you been doing?

00:43:45.256 --> 00:43:47.525
Can you call yourselves professionals
without trying to evolve?

00:43:47.592 --> 00:43:49.160
Zero points as performers.

00:43:49.227 --> 00:43:50.628
Don't upset the members!

00:43:50.695 --> 00:43:52.930
Seven members are too many.
Five would be reasonable.

00:43:52.997 --> 00:43:54.532
We won't get rid of any member!

00:43:54.599 --> 00:43:55.833
You're a loser if you can't do it.

00:43:55.900 --> 00:43:56.901
Impressive, Ms. Park.

00:43:56.968 --> 00:43:58.836
We'll hold a second audition
for NAZE.